Description:
Nous achetons des fermes pour y pérenniser une activité agricole.
Nous offrons aux agriculteurs un portage foncier long terme et sans frais, financé par un parc agrivoltaïque sur une partie des terres.

Nos engagements :
1. Pérennisation d’une activité agricole par le portage foncier à long terme, sans frais ;
2. Acquisitions foncières au juste prix du marché, pas de surenchères, pas de spéculation ;
3. Projets agricoles à haute performance humaine, économique et environnementale ;
4. Transparence et partenariats avec les acteurs institutionnels.

SOCIETE AGRO ALIMENTAIRE DU KIVU ET DE L'EDUCATION (S.AA.K.E)
1. Company/Institution: S.AAK.E is  an Agro-Pastoral, Food and Industrial company based on the production, processing and marketing of goods and services.
In its creation, it aims to improve food and social living conditions in rural areas in particular and in the province of South Kivu in general.
As noted above; SAKE ET Frères is a company with a dual vocation: commercial and humanitarian (non-profit).
Our activities are:
a. Livestock: here we raise different species:

  Guinea pig;
  Rabbit;
  Pig
  Hen
  Goat;
  Cow.

b. Agriculture: here we are talking about cultivating the soil by means of different varieties, appropriate seeds according to the medium, period and time.

 Sorghum
 Legume in general
 Taro
 Banana
 Reforestation (ecological and environmental protection)
 And others.

c. Fishing: consists in setting up a system of artisanal fishing by the construction of fish ponds: fish farming.


2. Vision: ‘hollow belly has no ear; you do not live to eat but eat to live":

 Improve the education of children;
 Support peasant initiatives;
 Improving the living conditions of farmers;
 Developing a good business climate in the rural environment;
 Eradicate hunger and poverty through healthy, balanced and diversified food.

3. Mission:

 Increase peasant productivity: in agriculture, breeding and marketing of goods and services;
 Ensuring appropriate education;
 Protecting the child: combating child malnutrition;
 Improving the food conditions of farmers.

4. Currency: our motto is based on four initial letters that form the rhyme "TCHA"
 Work;
 Consciousness;
 Honesty;
 Love.

B. Humanitarian (non-profit): In this vocation, we are experimenting, with the means put in place to eradicate hunger (zero hunger) and poverty (SDG I & II) in the rural environment; that is our generated goal.

